PS Anybody got info on how much damage the pet procs do in pvp? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/01 4:54:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Just looking at spdat.....<br>
<br>
Weak till lvl 9, not a fun class to start out with, compared to others.  Flash of light is great at low levels when dealing with non twinks of the same level.  Thought at lvl 15 the mana ratio on the pet heals is nice and it only gets better. At lvl 30 doiing 300 HP for only 75 mana is great, the mana cast for other classes is double for the same type of heal.<br>
<br>
On the dmg department, its all pet.  Getting a 80 dmg nuke at lvl 30, a lvl 24 shaman dot at lvl 40,venom of the snake at lvl 50 and a 450 dmg nuke for 200 mana at lvl 60 makes all their nukes/dot's pretty much useless.  Though a couple arent listed, but given the other spells they have it wont be anything great.<br>
<br>
The beastlord themselves are incredibly vunerable. Endure magic at lvl 40, once you get innfer flame you must wait 58 levels for your next HP buff.  They get a line of AC's buffs, but at abusrd levels that make them useless.<br>
Only melee skills will save them as the self buff's are pretty pitiful.<br>
<br>
Pets zoning with them will be extremly usefull, and a group of beastlords will be nasty, but on the overall pvp food chain they are on the lower end of the pecking chain due to their reliablity on pets.....atleast from my no rules Sullon Zek point of view.<br>
